  <div class="tg">Strong Contender</div>
  <h3>Tirzepatide (Mounjaro / Zepbound)</h3>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Type:</strong> Dual GIP/GLP-1 receptor agonist &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Dose Range:</strong> 2.5&ndash;15 mg weekly &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Route:</strong> Subcutaneous injection &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Developer:</strong> Eli Lilly &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Status:</strong> FDA-approved for weight management &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Best For:</strong> Proven efficacy with regulatory approval</p>
</div>

<p>Before retatrutide existed, tirzepatide broke new ground as the first dual GIP/GLP-1 receptor agonist approved for weight loss. Patients consistently lost 20&ndash;22% of body weight in the SURMOUNT trials (<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35658024/">Jastreboff et al., 2022</a>).</p>

<p>The innovation wasn't just in combining mechanisms. GIP receptor activation appears to enhance GLP-1's effects while reducing digestive side effects, making higher doses tolerable where previous GLP-1 drugs caused significant nausea.</p>

<p>Tirzepatide's success paved the way for the triple-action retatrutide and demonstrated that multi-receptor targeting was the future of metabolic medicine.</p>

<!-- ========== SEMAGLUTIDE ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>Semaglutide: The Proven Foundation</h2>

<div class="cd ct">
  <div class="tg">Most Studied</div>
  <h3>Semaglutide (Wegovy / Ozempic)</h3>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Type:</strong> GLP-1 receptor agonist &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Dose Range:</strong> 0.25&ndash;2.4 mg weekly &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Route:</strong> Subcutaneous or oral &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Developer:</strong> Novo Nordisk &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Status:</strong> FDA-approved &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Best For:</strong> First-line option with largest evidence base</p>
</div>

<p>No peptide has done more to change weight loss medicine than <a href="/articles/semaglutide-weight-loss-guide">semaglutide</a>. Originally developed for type 2 diabetes, researchers noticed an unexpected benefit: patients kept losing weight well beyond glucose control.</p>

<p>What many don't realize is that semaglutide's effects go beyond appetite suppression. It actually changes food preferences by reducing cravings for high-fat, high-sugar foods at the brain level (<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35441470/">Blundell et al., 2023</a>). Functional MRI studies show it dampens reward-center activity when viewing hyperpalatable foods.</p>

<p>The secret is semaglutide's exceptional half-life, which allows once-weekly dosing that maintains constant GLP-1 receptor activation. This neurobiological impact helps explain why it succeeds where willpower-based approaches fail.</p>

<div class="g2">
  <div class="mc">
    <h4 style="color:var(--teal);">Advantages</h4>
    <p>Largest clinical evidence base of any weight-loss peptide. Available in oral form (Rybelsus). FDA-approved with well-characterized safety profile. Proven cardiovascular benefits in SELECT trial.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="mc">
    <h4 style="color:var(--red);">Limitations</h4>
    <p>Lower total weight loss than dual or triple agonists. GI side effects common during titration. Weight regain after discontinuation without behavioral changes. Supply constraints ongoing.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ========== AOD-9604 ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>AOD-9604: The Direct Fat Signal</h2>

<div class="cd ca">
  <div class="tg">Targeted Lipolysis</div>
  <h3>AOD-9604 (Anti-Obesity Drug Fragment)</h3>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Type:</strong> Growth hormone fragment (aa 177&ndash;191) &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Typical Dose:</strong> 300 mcg daily &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Route:</strong> Subcutaneous injection &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Origin:</strong> Monash University, Australia &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Status:</strong> Research compound &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Best For:</strong> Stubborn localized fat deposits</p>
</div>

<p>While most weight loss peptides work through appetite or metabolism, <a href="/articles/aod-9604-fat-loss-peptide-guide">AOD-9604</a> takes a radically different approach. Developed from the C-terminus of human growth hormone, this fragment directly signals fat cells to release stored triglycerides without growth hormone's side effects.</p>

<p>Researchers spent years trying to isolate growth hormone's metabolic benefits from its growth-promoting effects. The breakthrough came when they discovered that just a small fragment (amino acids 177&ndash;191) could activate fat metabolism specifically.</p>

<p>Unlike systemic metabolism boosters, AOD-9604 works locally at fat deposits. This makes it particularly interesting for stubborn areas that resist diet and exercise.</p>

<!-- ========== TESAMORELIN ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>Tesamorelin: The Belly Fat Specialist</h2>

<div class="cd cr">
  <div class="tg">Visceral Fat Focus</div>
  <h3>Tesamorelin (Egrifta)</h3>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Type:</strong> GHRH analog &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Typical Dose:</strong> 1&ndash;2 mg daily &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Route:</strong> Subcutaneous injection &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Developer:</strong> Theratechnologies &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Status:</strong> FDA-approved (lipodystrophy) &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Best For:</strong> Visceral abdominal fat reduction</p>
</div>

<p>Visceral fat (the dangerous abdominal fat surrounding organs) responds poorly to most weight loss approaches. Tesamorelin changes that by specifically targeting growth hormone releasing hormone receptors.</p>

<p>Originally developed for HIV-related lipodystrophy, researchers discovered it had remarkable precision for reducing waist circumference. Clinical data shows 15&ndash;18% visceral fat reduction in just 6 months (<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20829745/">Falutz et al., 2010</a>).</p>

<p>The key to tesamorelin lies in its pulsatile delivery. By mimicking the body's natural growth hormone pulses, it avoids the insulin resistance issues seen with constant GH exposure. This makes it uniquely suited for <a href="/articles/metabolic-stack-tesamorelin-5amino1mq-aod9604">metabolic syndrome</a> patients who need abdominal fat reduction but can't risk worsening glucose control.</p>

<!-- ========== CJC/IPAMORELIN ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>CJC-1295/Ipamorelin: The Natural Amplifier</h2>

<div class="cd cp">
  <div class="tg">GH Secretagogue Stack</div>
  <h3>CJC-1295 + Ipamorelin Combination</h3>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Type:</strong> GHRH analog + GH secretagogue &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Typical Dose:</strong> 300 mcg each, evening &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Route:</strong> Subcutaneous injection &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Status:</strong> Research compounds &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Best For:</strong> Gradual recomposition with wellness benefits</p>
</div>

<p>This combination represents a different philosophy. Instead of introducing new signals, it amplifies your body's own growth hormone production. CJC-1295 extends GH release duration while ipamorelin boosts pulse amplitude.</p>

<p>The result is a natural rhythm enhancement that improves fat metabolism without the supraphysiological peaks of direct GH injection. Unlike synthetic GH, this stack preferentially targets fat cells over growth plates, making it safer for adults.</p>

<p>The gradual fat loss it produces (1&ndash;2 pounds weekly) comes with valuable side benefits: better sleep, improved skin quality, and faster recovery from exercise. It's the slower, steadier option with broader wellness upside.</p>

<!-- ========== MOTS-c ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>MOTS-c: The Mitochondrial Optimizer</h2>

<div class="cd cb">
  <div class="tg">Emerging Research</div>
  <h3>MOTS-c (Mitochondrial Open Reading Frame)</h3>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Type:</strong> Mitochondrial-derived peptide &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Typical Dose:</strong> 5 mg, 3x/week &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Route:</strong> Subcutaneous injection &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Discovery:</strong> 2015, USC &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Status:</strong> Research compound &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Best For:</strong> Metabolic optimization, exercise mimicking</p>
</div>

<p>Discovered in 2015, <a href="/articles/mots-c-mitochondrial-peptide">MOTS-c</a> represents an entirely new class of metabolic regulators. This mitochondrial-derived peptide communicates between the cell's energy factories and nucleus, reprogramming how cells source their fuel.</p>

<p>The most exciting aspect is its exercise-mimicking effects. MOTS-c activates AMPK pathways normally triggered only by intense physical activity. This makes it particularly valuable for those who can't exercise vigorously due to joint issues or time constraints.</p>

<p>Animal studies show it prevents diet-induced obesity even with high fat intake. During calorie restriction, it shifts energy sourcing toward fat while preserving glucose for the brain.</p>

